MongoDB provides a wide range of query operators that allow you to perform complex queries. These operators include comparison operators (e.g., $gt, $lt, $eq), logical operators (e.g., $and, $or, $not), array operators (e.g., $in, $all), and more.

üí† Basic Syntax

To perform a query in MongoDB, you need to use the "find()" method, which takes a document as a parameter. The document contains the query conditions and can have one or more fields to specify the criteria for the query.
